    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a fresh Ph.D. in Nursing Science at Penn State University. As a nursing researcher and nurse data scientist, I am conducting data mining projects on chronic illness and disability research. In addition to my dissertation research titled &amp;ldquo;Exploring Family Caregiving Experiences in Heart Failure: Utilization of Machine-Assisted Text Analysis,&amp;rdquo; I have been actively involved in diverse research projects such as &amp;ldquo;Exploring the trajectory of illness among people with advanced heart failure,&amp;rdquo; &amp;quot; The use of the Seattle Heart Model to guide palliative care referrals in heart failure,&amp;rdquo;  &amp;ldquo;Trends in self-management among adults with heart failure,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Analyzing longitudinal data using multi-level modelling to understand the trends of psychological well-being among the LGBTQ population,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Development of a clinical ethics education program for nurses,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Concept analysis of spirituality,&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Investigating the prevalence of Oxaliplatin-induced peripheral neuropathy by using electroni patient records.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
